{"title":"SiS Introduces New Beta Fuel Nutrition Line for long rides","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/15/sis-introduces-beta-fuel/","date":1626336057000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Today, London-based Science in Sport (‘SiS’) introduced its new Beta Fuel nutrition products, specially engineered for endurance athletes. It heralds the line as a “complete fueling solution” with a new MDX to fructose ratio optimized for carbohydrate absorption. It’s now hitting the consumer market after an internal trial period that started in 2018.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" alt=\"sis beta fuel\" width=\"1999\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1999w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-1536x1024.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-1920x1280.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1999px) 100vw, 1999px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x323/rscb25/ng:webp/ngcb25\" ezoid=\"0.48090396589872175\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1999w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-1536x1024.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-1920x1280.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130717/CC-SIS-0071-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 630w\"></p><p>A drink powder, gel, and bar are all on deck. Here’s what we know.</p><h2>Beta Fuel Development</h2><p>Beta Fuel first appeared on the world stage of <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/05/20/nutrition-roundup-tasty-new-treats-from-skratch-labs-honey-stinger-safe-catch/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">athletic nutrition</a> during Giro d’Italia in 2018, and SiS has been refining it ever since. Professor James Morton, Director of Performance Solutions for SiS, points to lab work that changed the company’s mind and ultimately differentiated Beta Fuel.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031.jpg\" alt=\"sis lemon-lime fuel\" width=\"1999\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031.jpg 1999w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1999px) 100vw, 1999px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb25 src ng ngcb25 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031.jpg 1999w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14131252/CC-SIS-0031-630x420.jpg 630w\"></p><p>Testing included elements like monitored rides under controlled conditions at SiS facilities. Athletes got Beta Fuel as prescribed, and results were tracked. Through that research, they found that the ideal MDX to fructose ratio for carb uptake is 1:0.8 (updated from the traditional 2:1). That led to a bevy of claimed performance upgrades for Beta Fuel.</p><p>According to research cited by SiS, the 1:0.8 ratio enhances exogenous CHO oxidation by up to 17% when compared to the original 2:1 blend. It also claims to increase the percentage of carb oxidization from 62% to 74%.</p><p>SiS even says the ratio helps reduce stomach fullness and gastrointestinal distress. According to SiS, Beta Fuel is ideal for those training over 2.5 hours.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211.jpg\" alt=\"sis gel for runners\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14130854/CC-SIS-0211-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/